The paper deals with a machine learning algorithm for multilabel classification and ranking, which falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG). The algorithm is based on 2nd-order descent methods, which are commonly used in optimization problems (cs.Optimization). The paper also discusses the use of upper-confidence bounds, which is a popular technique in reinforcement learning (cs.AI). The algorithm is tested on real-world multilabel datasets, which involves natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper presents regret bounds, which is a concept from online learning (cs.DS).
